com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1684<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/19/02 11:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> Could a mnew nation be created which was fully nuclearised. Having not signed any treaties with other nations yet. Able to adopt nuclear power plants, weapons and space rockets? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 642<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/20/02 5:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> It would have to be a rich nation, nuclear isn't cheap.<br>
<br>
Perhaps if Bill Gates bought an island somewhere... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1685<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/20/02 7:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> Nuclear weapons arsenals would be essential. The US is rather fond of forcing their own policies down other nations throats. Having the capability to bite back would dampen any empire notions among US politicians. Avoid a 'wag the dog' scenario. India never even signed the test ban treaties but was punished with sanctions nonetheless. Thats tantamount to an announcement of war. Such action against Japan in the 40's resulted in Pearl Harbour and US involvement in the second world war. Therefore a new nuclear nation would have to be totally independant aswell. Rich in natural resources so it can rely on its own raw materials for awhile. Then when the US tries to impose its will, the new country could leisurely look elsewhere for trade. Russia doesn't mind selling reactors and hiring out personnele. I suppose it's possible. One of those rogue russian states turned independant country might manage it. They are newly formed governments with Nukes and plants left behind by Russia. <br>
I rather like the idea of buying an island though. Perhaps even an island chain. It doesn't necessarily have to large. Fifty kilometres by twenty should suffice. Rocket tests could be conducted out at sea within the islands territorial limits.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hamster>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/20/02 9:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> Are there privately owned islands out there that aren't under the jurisdiction of any country's laws?  I'd love to buy some real estate here in the USA and declare it my own country but something tells me that isn't going to fly over to well.  I guess if you got enough people on your island who demanded independence and had smuggled in nuclear weapons to boot and let the presiding gov't know that, maybe you could get away with it.  You could create a situation similiar to that between China and Taiwan.  China thinks it owns Taiwan, but because Taiwan is going to bite back if China does anything, China &quot;allows&quot; Taiwan to exist as it sees fit.  I get the feeling though if the island &quot;belonged&quot; the USA you'd probably be ducking from bombs anyway.  Better to buy an island from some poor country that can't do anything to you.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1690<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/22/02 1:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> It's happened. Remember the Cuban Missile Crisis.<br>
<br>
I was thinking of Taiwan aswell. They are in a precarious situation though. They are a relatively new nation but hardly anyone recognises them as such. Fear of upsetting mainland China has seen to that. They are caught between the two big boys. China and the US. They can bite back and China knows it but having US protection doesn't hurt. Bush recently granted them new military radar technology. Taiwan has nuclear capability but if it was to go further and build nuclear rockets for space it could upset precious relations with the US 'AND' put the fear of God into mainland China who would not miss the military implications. A rocket capable of delivering people to Mars could easily take a massive hydrogen bomb to Beijing. Taiwan wouldn't dare risk it I think. The political unstable region would make it a foolhardy thing to try.<br>
Another option to buying a nation would be staging a coup. Find a suitable country and give some rebel faction enough weapons to take over. As hero of the resistance you can call in a few favours and the new Government would owe you big time. Either that or buying a political party and votes. Which is more american and negates the risk of US military forces coming over to restore the last corrupt government back into office. A whole list of nations come to mind. There are quite a few Kingdoms still remaining. Tonga is one. A number of hated dictators out there aswell.<br>
<br>
Christopher Skase had planned to build his own Island. True story. Out of floating sections it would be built out in international waters as a Tax Haven for the rich wanting to stay rich and preferably become even richer. Unfortunately for him he died before the deal could be set in motion. The law seems to be that if a new island rises out of the sea within international waters then it is up for grabs by whoever claims it first. Islands do frequently rise and disapear again between Japan and Korea. They are a source of constant squabbling between the two neighbours who each want to claim it as their own for reasons of military advantage and national prestige.<br>
<br>
Wouldn't it be nice if we could create our own island and claim ownership of it. Perhaps using a little atomics to cause seafloor upheaval? LOL. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/utmayes1965.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tmayes1965</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/23/02 2:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> The appropriate place to build a new nuclear and spacefaring<br>
nation state is the planet of Mars. If anybody on earth wants<br>
to interfere:  then let the real Martians give the earth a taste<br>
of the real ( War of the Worlds ).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 1691<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/23/02 8:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> Kind of a catch 42. To get there you need a nuclearised spacefaring nation. I've seen plans for thermal reactor rockets and they look absurdly simple to construct. There are top notch engineers and physicists presently starving in Russia. If they had somewhere to work which allowed them to get on with it then I daresay they could achieve far greater results than the ROVER program ever did. Rockets with maybe triple the power of a shuttle booster. A handful of launches and a flag would be on Mars. Sitting atop the base there. <br>
Having not signed the space treaties nobody could argue about them owning the Planet. Especially if they get a fleet of ships built to guard their interests. I can just imagine the US President biting his nails with worry.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/utmayes1965.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tmayes1965</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/24/02 12:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Nuclear Nation.</span><hr size=1> Nuclear power is very desirable for use to explore.<br>
and settle mars, but it is not required in order<br>
 to do this.<br>
 <br>
 Solar sail propelled  ships based in leo  can make<br>
 exellent martian  space freighters. Solar electric arc<br>
jet and resistojet propulsion systems can provide the<br>
same specific impulse that you would get from a nuclear<br>
thermal rocket, but at a much lower thrust level. It only<br>
takes about  3 km/sec to break out of earth orbit and <br>
head for mars, and venus.<br>
 <br>
 Any system that can accelerate  continously at 1<br>
